title: Empowers public service commission to provide for refund of excess revenues by telephone corporations
summary: Authorizes the public service commission to order a refund of any revenues which, when received by a telephone corporation, cause it to have earnings in excess of its authorized rate of return for the preceding year; provides that the public service commission may initiate a proceeding with respect to such refund at the end of any twelve-month period.
actClause: AN ACT to amend the public service law, in relation to excess earnings by telephone corporations
